@tuxitop I get what you mean but tbh this sounds complicated to me. Why not get rid of `LANG_COLOR` with the same key/values set in the default `colors` of yours which could then be overriden by users ?

My point is that your proposal lacks a clear mapping of `keymap name` - `color`, the `colors=(#xxx, #yyy)` does not make it clear what color goes for what keymap. It may looks simple to you because you **know** about the parsed output but common users don't.

So I still think it's better to *see* what keymap equals what color code somewhere and provide a simple and unique way to override the current default.

