Mostly because yaml is dumb, here's why:

```python
>>> yaml.load('args: [--ignore="E501,E302,E261,E701,E241,E126,E127,E128,W801,W391,F401,F403"]')
{'args': ['--ignore="E501', 'E302', 'E261', 'E701', 'E241', 'E126', 'E127', 'E128', 'W801', 'W391', 'F401', 'F403"']}
>>> yaml.load('args: [\'--ignore="E501,E302,E261,E701,E241,E126,E127,E128,W801,W391,F401,F403"\']')
{'args': ['--ignore="E501,E302,E261,E701,E241,E126,E127,E128,W801,W391,F401,F403"']}
# The correct one, notice it doesn't end up with internal quotes or split arguments
>>> yaml.load("args: ['--ignore=E501,E302o,E261,E701,E241,E126,E127,E128,W801,W391,F401,F403']")
{'args': ['--ignore=E501,E302o,E261,E701,E241,E126,E127,E128,W801,W391,F401,F403']}
>>> yaml.load('args: [--ignore=E501,E302o,E261,E701,E241,E126,E127,E128,W801,W391,F401,F403]')
{'args': ['--ignore=E501', 'E302o', 'E261', 'E701', 'E241', 'E126', 'E127', 'E128', 'W801', 'W391', 'F401', 'F403']}
```

