@aburbanol you encountered the reason why we don't recommend people use the libuvc backend on Linux -- it doesn't always terminate the camera correctly. Using the C++ API, the device is released on object destruction. Unfortunately with libuvc the device handle doesn't always get released so you need to unplug/replug -- known issue. The only recommended workaround is to use the V4L2 backend which you were having issues with previously.

Occasional bad numbers are expected, but regularly seeing them probably points to an issue with your USB connection or hardware platform (port, cable, host controller) and unfortunately not something we can solve in software.

@DongDongJu please open a new issue for your specific problem with all relevant details about your hardware, platform, and debugging steps so far. The same error messages are often used for a **large** variety of unrelated issues.

