Another possible (and more general) solution to this problem is something I suggested a while ago. If we add the following field to NodeProto, we can handle multiple operator arguments that can independently take 0, 1, or more real inputs.

   ```
  // The number of inputs for each argument of the operator takes
  // A formal parameter of the op may take a variable number of inputs
  // that is only known when this node is constructed.
  repeated int32 input_arg_count;
```
